# Java tests (required)

Full spec: [ai-kit/JAVA_TEST_CONVENTIONS.md](../../ai-kit/JAVA_TEST_CONVENTIONS.md)

## Hard rules

1. Read the doc above before editing `service/src/test/**`.
2. **Test only classes with logic** (`*Handler`, branching `*Service`, controllers with validation). Do not test models, mappers, or branchless config services.
3. **Single-entry Handler** (only `handle`): `@Test` on the outer class; no `@Nested`; `@DisplayName("Given ... -> ...")`; method names `given{Scenario}`.
4. **Multiple public methods**: one `@Nested` per method; `@DisplayName` = Java method name.
5. **Controllers (MockMvc)**: one `@Nested` per controller method, flat tests inside; `testHelper.request(...)`.
6. **Request validation coverage**: for request DTO constraints (e.g. `@NotNull`, `@Size(min/max)`, `@Pattern`), include invalid boundary cases per constrained field in controller tests; do not place request validation cases in handler tests.
7. **Controller parameterized invalid cases**: prefer `@ParameterizedTest` + `@MethodSource` with request objects; place the source right above the test.
8. **Controller authorization checks**: add authorization checks after request validation cases.
9. **Controller success cases**: keep one success scenario per controller method; move extra business branches to handler tests.
10. Extend `SpringBootIntegrationTests`; call `testHelper.clearAll()` in `@BeforeEach`.
11. Test data: `AuthData` / `UserData` + `TestConst.UID_*`; encode passwords with `PasswordEncoder.encode`.
12. Use AssertJ; handler business logic via `@Autowired Handler` + `handle(...)`; HTTP validation via MockMvc.
13. **`@MockitoSpyBean` only on `SpringBootIntegrationTests`**; never on subclasses.
14. Section comments in each `@Test`: `// Given`, `// When`, `// Then` (or `// When / Then`).
15. Run from repo root: `./gradlew :service:test`.

## Handler template (single `handle`)

```java
@DisplayName("FooHandler")
class FooHandlerTest extends SpringBootIntegrationTests {

  @Autowired TestHelper testHelper;
  @Autowired FooHandler fooHandler;

  @BeforeEach
  void setup() {
    testHelper.clearAll();
  }

  @Test
  @DisplayName("Given invalid input -> throw ApiException")
  void givenInvalidInput() {
    // Given
    // When / Then
    assertThatThrownBy(() -> fooHandler.handle(request)).isInstanceOf(ApiException.class);
  }
}
```
